# Batch Process Standards

All long-running scripts should follow these rules.

## 1. Real-time Progress

- Show an overall progress bar.
- Show per-stage or per-item progress where practical.
- Save progress state to disk so another terminal can inspect it.
- Avoid silent long-running steps.

## 2. Resource Guard

- Slow down before CPU or memory saturation.
- Use the 70% threshold as the default guardrail.
- Pause between stages when the slowdown flag is active.

## 3. Checkpoint and Resume

- Save progress after each successful stage where practical.
- Stop cleanly on failure.
- Prefer resumable state over blind restarts.
